category: NEW WORDS IN THE 1600s
category comment: 

clue: What sayest thee? Dost thou mean this thing whereon beads are slid for counting?

response: an abacus

clue: The striped & brindled coat of yon cat now hath its own name, this

response: tabby

clue: Good news! No longer need we say "shedding its leaves at the end of its growing season"--herewith a word for that

response: deciduous

clue: From the zesty Italian tongue cometh this word for a large, plush residence; someday methinks it will have its own pants

response: palazzo

clue: My anatomist doth dub it the "hipbone basin" but I must inform him that it is now known by this word of 6 letters

response: the pelvis

